Explanation:
The solution iterates from 1 to n (inclusive) with a step of k. For each iteration, it extracts the last digit from the current number and adds it to the result vector. Then, it removes the last digit from the number by dividing it by 10. This process continues until the number becomes 0. Finally, it adds the number itself to the result vector. The solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it iterates n times, and a space complexity of O(n) due to the result vector.

